parameters:
"We'll be spotted by the man with sunglasses from here.
Let's find another place to break in."

(Yes, a back door! It looks like I can get inside from
here!)
Trespassing is a bit... you know.

"It seems like this place is a storeroom. There are all
sorts of things I don't recognize."

"I wonder what floor Makoto is on right now... For now, I
guess I'll head upstairs."

The goal of the interference event is to rescue the heroine.
If you succeed, you can avoid the NTR event that would occur
that week. On the other hand, if you fail even once, a
tragic ending will ensue. Everything depends on you. Please
decide the story's ending with your own hands.

"I wonder if Makoto entered this building?... For now, I'll
try going inside as well."

"This is private property. If you go any further inside...
Huh? You are..."

"Um, what is this building? I thought it was a hotel or
something..."

"Huh?... I guess it could look like that. But this is a
legitimate house built by someone named \c[10]Suzuki\c[0]."

"If you have the owner's permission, that's a different
story. But if you don't have any business here, please don't
enter."

"Ah, I see. I'm sorry... I just assumed it was some kind of
commercial facility..."

"No, it's fine as long as you understand. Just don't come in
here, alright? See ya."

(That guy with the sunglasses... He just mentioned Suzuki,
right? Could this building be that Suzuki's house?)

(But I can't imagine Makoto going to Suzuki's house... Maybe
it's just someone with the same name...?)

(...No good, thinking about it won't get me anywhere. If
only I could get inside that building and check for myself.)

"She's not coming out... Makoto... She couldn't possibly not
be here, right...?"

"Yes, I did it! Makoto came out! Just as I thought, she was
at this house!"

"It was just a glance, but she doesn't seem to have been
harmed, and it looks like she's been safely released!"

(But just to be sure, I should watch Makoto until she gets
home straight. I don't think anything else will happen, but
better safe than sorry.)

Afterward, Makoto had a puzzled look on her face the whole
time, but she didn't make any detours and went straight
home. At least for today, Suzuki shouldn't be able to lay a
hand on her.

There are still many questions left, like why Makoto went to
Suzuki's house in the first place. But having rescued her, I
was completely drained and fell asleep without being able to
think any further that day.

"Really... I'm sure I told you this is private property.
What you've done is a clear case of trespassing."

"You didn't seem to steal anything in particular... I'll let
it slide just this once. Go on, hurry back home."

"Trespassing... as if I knew... Release Makoto... let Makoto
go..."

"Makoto? What are you talking about? There's no one named
Makoto inside this building."

"That can't be...! Makoto went down this road. She must be
inside, I'm sure of it!"

"Nope, I really don't know. The only ones here are the
homeowner and... the call girl we ordered a while ago."

"From what you're saying, it doesn't seem like you actually
saw this Makoto person enter, did you?"

"Could it be a misunderstanding on your part? This Makoto
hasn't come here."

"I didn't actually see her, but... then where could Makoto
be..."

"How would I know? Look, you've realized it's a
misunderstanding. Now get lost."

(Is it really just my misunderstanding...? Or is this guy
lying...?)

(Either way, now that I've been found out, I can't sneak in
here anymore. There's nothing left for me to do...)

Unable to do anything further, I obediently left the
building and headed home. On the way back, I agonized over
whether to call the police, but decided against it, thinking
that it might backfire and I'd be charged with trespassing.

If only I had seen Makoto enter the building, I might have
had something to say. With that thought, I began to doubt
whether Makoto was really in that building at all.

As the man with sunglasses had said, I hadn't actually seen
Makoto enter the building with my own eyes. I had only
witnessed her going down that road.

It's not like the road ended in front of Suzuki's house, and
maybe a new dojo had been built further down the road, and
Makoto had gone there instead.

Makoto didn't go to Suzuki's house. It was all a
misunderstanding on my part. I forced myself to think
positively like that, trying to lift my sunken spirits.

I escaped into optimistic thoughts to distract myself from
my own pain. But that night, I couldn't sleep well, and I
woke up feeling terrible. I managed to leave the house with
a throbbing headache, but Makoto was nowhere to be seen
outside.
"It's kind of scary, maybe I should just go home..."

※Note: If you select the text in \c[10]red\c[0], it will
result in a \c[10]failed conquest\c[0].
I can't go back because I'm worried about Makoto!

It seemed like Makoto entered this building, but I,
intimidated by the man in sunglasses, ran away without doing
anything.

Honestly, I had never heard of a dojo being nearby, but I
convinced myself it must be new. However, I became worried
about Makoto afterwards and couldn't sleep well that night.

The next day. I had a terrible headache from lack of sleep,
but I decided to go to school. Surely I must have been
mistaken yesterday. I should be able to go to school with
Makoto today. With that thought, I opened the front door,
but Makoto was nowhere to be seen outside my house.
